29#include "bitstream.h"

31#define DEFAULT_BUFSIZE (128)
32
33BitStream *BitStream_new(void)
34{
35 BitStream *bstream;
36
37 bstream = (BitStream *)malloc(sizeof(BitStream));
38 if(bstream == NULL) return NULL;
39
40 bstream->length = 0;
41 bstream->data = (unsigned char *)malloc(DEFAULT_BUFSIZE);
42 if(bstream->data == NULL) {
43 free(bstream);
44 return NULL;
45 }
46 bstream->datasize = DEFAULT_BUFSIZE;
47
48 return bstream;
49}
50
51static int BitStream_expand(BitStream *bstream)
52{
53 unsigned char *data;
54
55 data = (unsigned char *)realloc(bstream->data, bstream->datasize * 2);
56 if(data == NULL) {
57 return -1;
58 }
59
60 bstream->data = data;
61 bstream->datasize *= 2;
62
63 return 0;
64}
65
66static void BitStream_writeNum(unsigned char *dest, int bits, unsigned int num)
67{
68 unsigned int mask;
69 int i;
70 unsigned char *p;
71
72 p = dest;
73 mask = 1 << (bits - 1);
74 for(i=0; i<bits; i++) {
75 if(num & mask) {
76 *p = 1;
77 } else {
78 *p = 0;
79 }
80 p++;
81 mask = mask >> 1;
82 }
83}
84
85static void BitStream_writeBytes(unsigned char *dest, int size, unsigned char *data)
86{
87 unsigned char mask;
88 int i, j;
89 unsigned char *p;
90
91 p = dest;
92 for(i=0; i<size; i++) {
93 mask = 0x80;
94 for(j=0; j<8; j++) {
95 if(data[i] & mask) {
96 *p = 1;
97 } else {
98 *p = 0;
99 }
100 p++;
101 mask = mask >> 1;
102 }
103 }
104}
105
106int BitStream_append(BitStream *bstream, BitStream *arg)
107{
108 int ret;
109
110 if(arg == NULL) {
111 return -1;
112 }
113 if(arg->length == 0) {
114 return 0;
115 }
116
117 while(bstream->length + arg->length > bstream->datasize) {
118 ret = BitStream_expand(bstream);
119 if(ret < 0) return ret;
120 }
121
122 memcpy(bstream->data + bstream->length, arg->data, arg->length);
123 bstream->length += arg->length;
124
125 return 0;
126}
127
128int BitStream_appendNum(BitStream *bstream, int bits, unsigned int num)
129{
130 int ret;
131
132 if(bits == 0) return 0;
133
134 while(bstream->datasize - bstream->length < bits) {
135 ret = BitStream_expand(bstream);
136 if(ret < 0) return ret;
137 }
138 BitStream_writeNum(bstream->data + bstream->length, bits, num);
139 bstream->length += bits;
140
141 return 0;
142}
143
144int BitStream_appendBytes(BitStream *bstream, int size, unsigned char *data)
145{
146 int ret;
147
148 if(size == 0) return 0;
149
150 while(bstream->datasize - bstream->length < size * 8) {
151 ret = BitStream_expand(bstream);
152 if(ret < 0) return ret;
153 }
154 BitStream_writeBytes(bstream->data + bstream->length, size, data);
155 bstream->length += size * 8;
156
157 return 0;
158}
159
160unsigned char *BitStream_toByte(BitStream *bstream)
161{
162 int i, j, size, bytes;
163 unsigned char *data, v;
164 unsigned char *p;
165
166 size = BitStream_size(bstream);
167 if(size == 0) {
168 return NULL;
169 }
170 data = (unsigned char *)malloc((size + 7) / 8);
171 if(data == NULL) {
172 return NULL;
173 }
174
175 bytes = size / 8;
176
177 p = bstream->data;
178 for(i=0; i<bytes; i++) {
179 v = 0;
180 for(j=0; j<8; j++) {
181 v = v << 1;
182 v |= *p;
183 p++;
184 }
185 data[i] = v;
186 }
187 if(size & 7) {
188 v = 0;
189 for(j=0; j<(size & 7); j++) {
190 v = v << 1;
191 v |= *p;
192 p++;
193 }
194 data[bytes] = v;
195 }
196
197 return data;
198}
199
200void BitStream_free(BitStream *bstream)
201{
202 if(bstream != NULL) {
203 free(bstream->data);
204 free(bstream);
205 }
206}
